        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued July 28 at 2:58PM EDT by NWS Detroit/Pontiac MI</headline>
        <description>At 258 PM EDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm over
Saline, moving east at 20 mph.

HAZARD...Wind gusts up to 50 mph and pea size hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects. Minor damage to outdoor objects is
possible.

Locations impacted include...
Saline, Milan, Manchester, Willis, Bridgewater, Pittsfield Township,
Whittaker, and Pleasant Lake.
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.

Torrential rainfall is also occurring with this storm and may lead to
localized flooding. Do not drive your vehicle through flooded
roadways.</instruction>
